covered: Valid Request: TC01 (minimal fields) and TC02 (all fields) cover successful updates with valid payloads
Headers/Authorization: TC05 (missing header) and TC09 (unauthorized) cover header/auth validation
Input Validation: TC06 (invalid accountId format), TC07 (invalid body), TC21 (unexpected formats), TC18 (malicious input) cover data validation and security
Non-Existing Resource / Error Handling: TC08 (non-existent account) and TC12 (server error) cover error responses for absent resources and server issues
Edge Cases: TC11 (empty body), TC10 (extra fields), TC22 (extra query params) cover handling of unusual input and query usage
Null Handling: TC03 and TC04 cover treatNullAsReset true/false scenarios
Partial Updates: TC19 (partial input) and TC20 (min/max values) cover updating subset fields and value bounds
Propagation/Integration: TC16 covers update propagation to dependent services
Performance/Concurrency: TC13 (large payload), TC14 (slow network/timeout), TC17 (concurrent updates) cover performance and concurrency aspects
Regression: TC15 ensures only intended field (email) updates
gaps: 403 Forbidden / insufficient permission scenarios not explicitly tested (beyond 401)
Rate limiting / throttling tests are missing
Caching behavior testing (ETag / Cache-Control) is not covered
Explicit test for disallowed partial updates (when partial updates should be rejected) is not present
Additional invalid payload variations and data type edge cases could be broadened
recommendations: Add a test for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient permissions and role-based access
Introduce rate limiting tests to validate throttling behavior
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for PUT responses
Add explicit scenarios where partial updates are rejected if not allowed, to complement TC19
Expand invalid payload coverage with more edge cases and data type mismatches
